{
    "name": "edinburgh",
    "displayName": "Edinburgh",
    "title": "Explore Edinburgh",
    "introduction": {
        "contentType": "hippostd:html",
        "value": "<p>It was in Scotland&#39;s capital city that JK Rowling started to plot the adventures of Harry and his friends. With cobbled streets, winding alleys and medieval architecture, the city certainly has a few things in common with the settings from the books and films. She wrote the early chapters in various caf&#233;s around the city&#39;s Old Town, before coming back to finish off the series from a peaceful suite in The Balmoral Hotel. It is also said that Hogwarts School was styled on Edinburgh&#8217;s Fettes College, a private school on the outskirts of Edinburgh&#8217;s west end new town. You could also try the Wizarding World of Edinburgh tour.</p>"
    },
